+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NaCEk6xDuqKut3xq5un1bP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I've completed a thorough exploration of the project. Here's my comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Overview\n\nThis is a **task queue system marathon project** called \"bench-task-queue\" - a 12-phase implementation of an in-memory task queue system from scratch, similar to systems like Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n**Root Configuration Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - Node package definition (type: \"module\", ES modules)\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config targeting ES2022, strict mode enabled\n- `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs` - ESLint configuration with TypeScript support\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Vitest testing framework config (10s timeout)\n- `/workspace/.gitignore` - Ignores node_modules/, dist/, *.tsbuildinfo\n- `/workspace/TASK.md` - Main task overview document\n\n**Source Code:**\n- `/workspace/src/` - Empty (only .gitkeep present) - this is where you build the implementation\n\n**Phase Requirements:**\n- `/workspace/phases/phase-01.md` through `/workspace/phases/phase-12.md` - All 12 detailed phase specifications\n\n## Dependencies\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- TypeScript 5.4.0\n- ESLint with TypeScript plugin\n- Vitest 2.0.0 with coverage plugin v8\n- @types/node 25.2.3\n\n**No runtime dependencies** - must be implemented purely in TypeScript/JavaScript with no external packages.\n\n## All 12 Phase Requirements\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Add tasks with payload, get unique ID, status, creation timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieve oldest pending task, transition to \"processing\"\n- Return null if no tasks\n- Query pending task count\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Multiple independent queues with names\n- Default queue if no name specified\n- Implicit queue creation on first task\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1 is highest, default 5)\n- Invalid priorities cause error\n- Higher priority (lower number) returned first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Tasks with delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks not returned until availability time\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (default 1s, 2s, 4s...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Base backoff: 1000ms default (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Failed tasks stay in failed state when retries exhausted\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Tasks with exhausted retries move to DLQ\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for retry\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Independent DLQ per named queue\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can specify dependencies on other task IDs\n- Task with unresolved dependencies is blocked\n- System checks when dependency completes if dependents unblock\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't auto-fail dependents\n- Query task dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting (limit processing state tasks)\n- Return null if concurrency limit reached, even with pending tasks\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Concurrency respects priority ordering\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task reports progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates, get notifications on changes\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Pending cancellation removes from queue\n- Processing cancellation updates status\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedules associate cron expressions with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism for testing\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other queue rules\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Task passes through middleware in order before handler\n- Each middleware gets task and \"next\" function\n- Middleware can skip task or modify it\n- Middleware errors mark task as failed\n- Handler/processing function registered per queue\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown signals system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Waits for processing tasks to complete (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancels tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register callbacks to run during shutdown\n- Returns summary: completed count, force-cancelled count, duration\n- Safe to call multiple times\n- Completes immediately if no processing tasks\n\n## Development Setup\n\n**Available Scripts:**\n```bash\nnpm run build    # TypeScript compilation to dist/\nnpm run lint     # ESLint check\nnpm run test     # Vitest run\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Notes:**\n- Export main API from `/workspace/src/index.ts`\n- All code under `/workspace/src/`\n- Later phases may require rethinking early decisions - design for extensibility\n- Tasks need unique IDs and lifecycle status tracking\n- Consider how features interact (priorities, delays, dependencies, etc.)\n\nThe src/ directory is completely empty and ready for implementation. This is a greenfield project where you'll build incrementally through all 12 phases."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7af29a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19251\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 27168</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09529994-9437-4374-896a-f6237220442e","uuid":"d53b4fe9-f783-48fe-87e8-848784c99699","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore this project. I need to understand:\n1. The full project structure (package.json, tsconfig, existing src files, etc.)\n2. ALL phase requirement files in phases/*.md - read every single one of them\n3. Any existing code in src/\n4. The TASK.md file\n\nRead every single file you find. Be very thorough - I need all 12 phase requirement files.","agentId":"a7af29a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I've completed a thorough exploration of the project. Here's my comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Overview\n\nThis is a **task queue system marathon project** called \"bench-task-queue\" - a 12-phase implementation of an in-memory task queue system from scratch, similar to systems like Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n**Root Configuration Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - Node package definition (type: \"module\", ES modules)\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config targeting ES2022, strict mode enabled\n- `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs` - ESLint configuration with TypeScript support\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Vitest testing framework config (10s timeout)\n- `/workspace/.gitignore` - Ignores node_modules/, dist/, *.tsbuildinfo\n- `/workspace/TASK.md` - Main task overview document\n\n**Source Code:**\n- `/workspace/src/` - Empty (only .gitkeep present) - this is where you build the implementation\n\n**Phase Requirements:**\n- `/workspace/phases/phase-01.md` thro